# Trading Strategy Repo — Agent Rules

## Repo Structure

```
trading-strategy/
├── .cursor/
│   ├── rules/
│   │   └── trading-agent.mdc         ← this file — always-on conventions
│   └── skills/
│       ├── analyse-tickers/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← research, scoring, output format
│       ├── log-trade-csv/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← CSV schema and writing rules
│       ├── track-outcomes/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← 14-day outcome lookback and CSV update
│       ├── browser-use/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← browser-use CLI automation (optional)
│       ├── indicators/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← TradingView: Fair Value Bands, weekly BX, daily B-Xtrender
│       ├── read-tradingview-chart/
│       │   └── SKILL.md              ← optional extra TradingView notes (profile Tim)
│       └── archived/
│           └── read-trendspider-chart/  ← historical TrendSpider helpers + SKILL (not live workflows)
├── strategies/
│   └── <strategy-name>/
│       ├── AGENT.md                  ← workflow steps for this strategy's agent
│       ├── config.md                 ← scan URL, universe, style, entry filters
│       ├── trades-log.csv            ← trade log scoped to this strategy only
│       └── report.md                 ← current report, overwritten each run
└── README.md
```

## Rules for All Agents in This Repo

- Every strategy agent MUST load `analyse-tickers` before running. Trade-entry strategies should also load `log-trade-csv` and `track-outcomes`; watchlist-only strategies may define and maintain their own `watchlist.csv` workflow in strategy-local docs.
- Agents that perform **TradingView** visual confirmation MUST also load **`indicators`** (`.cursor/skills/indicators/SKILL.md`) and MUST use **`browser-use --profile "Tim" --headed`** — not Puppeteer or headless default Chromium (login + saved chart `z25AhAlV` require profile Tim)
- Each strategy writes ONLY to its own strategy-local CSV file (`trades-log.csv` or `watchlist.csv`) — never to another strategy's log
- Never overwrite existing CSV rows — always append
- Never fabricate financial data; if data is unavailable, note it and downrank the ticker
- Always check for upcoming earnings dates before recommending an entry

## Adding a New Strategy

1. Create `strategies/<name>/config.md` — scan URL, universe, trading style, and custom entry filters
2. Create `strategies/<name>/AGENT.md` — load the required skills, then define the workflow steps (use an existing strategy as template)
3. Create the strategy CSV file — use `trades-log.csv` for trade-entry strategies or a strategy-local `watchlist.csv` schema for watchlist-only workflows
4. Create `strategies/<name>/report.md` — placeholder; will be overwritten on first run
